    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R028"/>
    <hasWarningHeadline>Serum Electrolyte Abnormalities</hasWarningHeadline>
    <hasWarningText>The high sodium load associated with the use of CONTEPO may result in changes in serum electrolytes, such as increased levels of sodium and decreased levels of potassium, calcium and phosphorus. A low-sodium diet is recommended during CONTEPO treatment. Monitor serum electrolyte levels and fluid status during CONTEPO treatment</hasWarningText>
