  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE180">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Methaemoglobinaemia"/>
    <rdfs:label>methaemoglobinaemia</rdfs:label>
    <hasDurationOf>Not specified</hasDurationOf>
    <hasPattern rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Very_rare"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R035"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R281"/>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>Methemoglobinemia (MetHb) is a rare blood disorder that affects how red blood cells deliver oxygen throughout your body. Not everyone has symptoms, but nearly all people with this condition have skin, nails or lips that are a distinctive shade of blue or purple.</hasSideEffectDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN018">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN018</rdfs:label>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Increased discomfort or nausea.</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Alcohol does not directly interact, but it may worsen side effects like dizziness or stomach upset.</hasInteractionDescription>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Limit or avoid alcohol during therapy.</hasManagementAdvice>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R026"/>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S008"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN249">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN249</rdfs:label>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Because less Macrobid reaches your bloodstream and urine, the infection may not get treated properly. You may have ongoing symptoms of urinary tract infection like pain, burning, or frequent urination.</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Antacids that contain magnesium trisilicate can stick to Macrobid in your stomach and gut, which lowers the amount of the antibiotic that your body can absorb. This makes Macrobid less able to fight the bacteria causing your infection.</hasInteractionDescription>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Avoid taking these antacids while on Macrobid. If you must take an antacid, separate the doses by at least 2-3 hours. Always tell your doctor or pharmacist about any antacids you are using.</hasManagementAdvice>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R161"/>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S168"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#Gastrointestinal">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>Gastrointestinal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#SideEffect"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE143">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Vomiting"/>
    <rdfs:label>Vomiting</rdfs:label>
    <hasDurationOf>Not Specified</hasDurationOf>
    <hasPattern rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Happens_during_multiple-dose_regimen"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R038"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R057"/>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>Forceful ejection stomach contents through the mouth.</hasSideEffectDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#W077">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#PregnancyAndLactation"/>
    <rdfs:label>W077</rdfs:label>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R031"/>
    <hasWarningHeadline>Pregnancy</hasWarningHeadline>
    <hasWarningText>Comazole is contraindicated during pregnancy. If pregnancy cannot be excluded, possible risks should be balanced against the expected therapeutic effect. Comazole should not be given during pregnancy especially in late pregnancy because of risk of kernicterus.</hasWarningText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE220">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Glossitis"/>
    <rdfs:label>Glossitis</rdfs:label>
