    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN260</rdfs:label>
    <hasClinicalEffects>The medicine may not work as effectively, and the infection may persist or return.</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Urinary alkalinisers increase urine pH (make urine more alkaline), which can decrease the activity of Nitrofurantoin.</hasInteractionDescription>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Avoid unnecessary use of urinary alkalinisers while taking Nitrofurantoin. Inform your doctor about all medications being used.</hasManagementAdvice>
